National Security Advisor Tom Donilon traveled to Beijing to prepare for the upcoming meeting between President Obama and President Xi Jinping. Donilon had meetings with senior Chinese officials, including President Xi Jinping, Vice Premier Wang Yang, State Councilor Yang Jiechi, National Development and Reform Commission Vice Chairman Liu He, Foreign Minister Wang Yi, and General Fan Changlong. The purpose of the meetings was to discuss U.S.-China relations, regional and global challenges, and cooperation on issues such as North Korea, cyber-security, climate change, stability in Asia, and expanding military ties. Donilon also emphasized the importance of coordination on the global economy, bilateral economic relations, and continued dialogue on human rights.